Dutch filmmaker Theo van Gogh, who had received threats over a controversial film he made about Islam, was shot and stabbed to death Tuesday while cycling on an Amsterdam street.
The alleged assailant, identified as having dual Dutch and Moroccan nationality, was arrested and two people were injured in a shootout with police after the attack in broad daylight early Tuesday.
Police said that the suspect in the killing was a 26-year-old man with dual Dutch and Moroccan nationality.
Several witnesses said the man was dressed in an Islamic robe with a long beard.
